==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, originally a diminutive form of the base of [[ball]]. 

Word is no longer used in modern use, but has the alternate word of "bollocks", holding the same distinction.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'bæallʊkaz/}}

===Noun===
'''beallucas''' ''m'' ''pl''
# [[testicle]]s.

